<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> &quot;Angela&quot; &lt;tenacio...@aol.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-02-17T00:09:00 </POSTDATE>
Thank you all for your prayers.  The surgery went well.  My doctor was
quite surprised at how bad the inflammation and impingement of the
nerve were.  It was much worse than the emg and nerve conduction study
showed. He theorized that some of my meds may have masked the
damage.

Before surgery, he said I could remove the bandage on Sunday and
shower with it unprotected and he wanted me to do gentle stretching
and range of motion exercises with it. After surgery, he said NOT to
unbandage it, had it immobilized, and wants to see me Monday a.m. to
unbandage it and check it out.

It is quite painful and he is concerned about pain management over the
weekend but didn't know what else to give me along with what I already
take... oxycontin 40, lortab 10, soma or flexeril (day, night
respectively).  My pain management doc's assistant told me to let the
surgeon decide what to give me post-surgically when I called earlier
this week in an attempt to NOT wind up where I am now.  My meds barely
(if at all) take the edge off.  And since they gave a massive dose of
steroids along with being wired from the after-effects of the
anesthesia, i can't sleep.

Anyway, sorry to ramble on, whining. just wanted to let you all know I
was home and all things considered, it went well.  Again, thank you
all for your prayers.

Angela
